<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 07 at 3:28PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT CENTRAL MONTGOMERY COUNTY
THROUGH 400 PM EDT...
At 327 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Merrimac, or over Christiansburg, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Blacksburg...
Christiansburg...
Shawsville...
Mc Donalds Mill...
Elliston-Lafayette...
Merrimac...
and Elliston.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
